Colombian Stocks: Cementos Argos, Pacific Rubiales, ETB Rise

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-08-16T20:26:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/colombian-stocks-cementos-argos-pacific-rubiales-etb-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.6 percent to 13,489.13 while the
Colcap Index gained 0.6 percent to 1,620.63.  Cementos Argos (CEMARGOS CB),  Colombia ’s biggest cement
maker, rose 2.8 percent to 11,000 pesos. President  Juan Manuel Santos  announced Aug. 12 a reduction in tariffs on raw materials
that will save importers $340 million in 2012, including on
construction materials, according to an e-mailed statement on
the presidential website.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota (ETB)  SA, the
phone company serving Colombia’s capital, rose 2.2 percent to
552 pesos, a two-week high. Leading candidate Gustavo Petro said
if elected mayor of Bogota he would seek to merge ETB with other
state-controlled companies in the capital that manage water,
energy and transportation, according to RCN.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 0.2 percent
to 46,300 pesos. Rubiales’s share price has a year-end upside
potential of 66 percent on the company’s “solid fundamental
performance as shown through consistent compliance with
production targets, high rate of exploratory success and growing
levels of profitability and liquidity,” Samuel David Garcia, an
analyst at brokerage Valores Bancolombia, said in a report e-
mailed today.  The shares are being traded at multiples lower than peers,
the report said. The shares have fallen 27 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
